article.description: Oregon State 72, U of the Pacific 43
article.headline: Oregon State 72, U of the Pacific 43
article.linkText: Oregon State 72, U of the Pacific 43
article.story:
CORVALLIS, Ore. (AP) -- Shannon Howell had 19 points and four
rebounds to lead Oregon State to a 72-43 win over Pacific on
Tuesday.

Mandy Close scored 12 points and Casey Bunn added 11 for the
Beavers (4-5) in their final game before the start of Pac-10 play.

Jessie Menkens led Pacific (2-5) with 11 points and four steals.

Oregon State surged to a 41-11 halftime lead. Pacific shot just
3-of-20 and had 20 turnovers in the opening 20 minutes.

Things got worse in the second half for the Tigers, who trailed
by as many as 42. With less than seven minutes to play, they had 31
points and 29 turnovers.

Oregon State got sloppy with the ball in garbage time, and the
teams combined for 58 turnovers.
